body:
#SaveGoodBehavior

Hey friends, I’m reaching out in an effort to get a spectacular show saved. For those of you who watch Good Behavior, as you may or may not know, it has been cancelled. I feel its only reason for being cancelled was the lack of awareness for it. Very few people were aware the second season ever aired or that the show got cancelled back in November (myself included). So I’m asking for a little help in raising awareness for this show and for it to be rescued.

If you know the show, you know what I’m talking about. If you haven’t seen it, please check it out! To those of you watching Killing Eve or watched Banshee, this is a show for you. It’s about the misadventures (and love story) of a thief and a hitman, but there’s so much more to the show as well. Overall, it’s witty, edgy, and clever, but just hasn’t had the time to reach a larger audience.

Rarely does a show have so much heart and potential or keep you on your toes the way Good Behavior does. The story is far from over and I hope that others will recognize this and rescue the show. So please give it a chance and help me save a show with a wonderful plot and an amazing cast. Please reblog and sign the petition in the link to help rescue it!

https://www.change.org/p/network-executives-bring-back-good-behavior

summary: So maybe it is not one of the most important things to think about, but it is definitely what i find myself thinking about in...
body:
Did Anna and Oksana meet while she was in high school?

So maybe it is not one of the most important things to think about, but it is definitely what i find myself thinking about in the middle of a night.

Of course, looking at the building of where Anna and Eve first meet, we can be sure it is a college or a university.

But here are some things about that box and the photos in it that tell me she was definitely her school teacher.

So, first, it is nice photo.

What we see here is a very ordinary graduation photo of any russian high schooler. It is a tradition to wear such ribbons, although they don’t necessarily have to be this patriotic.

So how does Anna have this picture? Would Oksana be that kind of person to give it to her or would Anna be that kind of stalker ro find this photo by herself? Something tells me it is neither. Anna just has this photo because she was these kids teacher.

And here we have this.

It is obviously some olympiad kind of thing, for there are too little kids for this to be graduation and high school certificates dont look like this. And Anna is on it with Oksana. And Anna is her French language teacher. In universities people dont really do olympiads and take pics with certificates, though it still does not quite prove the point. Maybe that is some really weiiiird university, for all we know.

This picture though, wonder who took it? Maybe we should not really wonder, because it was a photo from their graduation album. Yes, that’s possible. In graduation albums there is often a portrait of a student. In universities people dont do this, or at least I have not done it EVER.

And there are also these photos.

Who took these? — a biggest mystery.

So in the end, all I want to say is that it is either Anna was her school teacher and it will be simpler to understand how they could have bonded so well (in school there is a deeper connection between a teacher and a pupil) or the writers that dont know russian education system well enough just… kind of messed it up.
